Dependency Installation - Linux
For the application to be able to capture dashboards/reports on a Linux-based Search-Head the following components must be installed:

- CasperJS (tested against version 1.1.4-1)
- PhantomJS (tested against version 2.1.1)
- ImageMagick (tested against version 6.9.9-8-Q16-static)

IMPORTANT: UsingaversionofCasperJS/PhantomJS from within your package-manager will in most cases not function at all or will create broken screen-captures, due to inconsistencies between the mainline versions and the distro-specific versions.
Always download the CasperJS/PhantomJS code directly from their respective websites.

For simplicity, it is recommended that each package is downloaded/installed as follows:
CasperJS: (as root)

- wget -O /opt/casperjs.zip https://github.com/casperjs/casperjs/archive/1.1.4-1.zip
- unzip /opt/casperjs.zip -d /opt
- rm -f /opt/casperjs.zip
- ln -sf /opt/casperjs-1.1.4-1 /opt/casperjs

PhantomJS: (as root)
- wget -O /opt/phantomjs.tbz2 https://bitbucket.org/ariya/phantomjs/downloads/phantomjs-2.1.1-linux-x86_64.tar.bz2
- tar -xjpv /opt/phantomjs.tbz2 -C /opt
- rm -f /opt/phantomjs.tbz2
- ln -sf /opt/phantomjs-2.1.1-linux-x86_64 /opt/phantomjs

ImageMagick: (as root)
- Either ‘yum -y install ImageMagick’ or ‘apt-get -y install imagemagick’ (depending on distro)

For larger environments, it is possible to package the required dependencies within the application and have them distributed centrally, however that is not covered in this document due to the size of the application increasing substantially.

Dependency Installation – Windows

For the application to be able to capture dashboards/reports on a Windows-based Search-Head the following components must be installed:

- CasperJS (tested against version 1.1.4-1)
- PhantomJS (tested against version 2.1.1)
- ImageMagick (tested against version 6.9.9-8-Q16-static)


Always download the CasperJS/PhantomJS/ImageMagick code directly from their respective websites.

For Windows, the following format of each file should be downloaded:
- CasperJS: casperjs-1.1.4-1.zip 
- PhantomJS: phantomjs-2.1.1-windows.zip
- ImageMagick: ImageMagick-6.9.9-8-Q16-x64-static.exe

For consistency, it is recommended that you install/extract each required dependency to the following folders (on your primary drive):
- CasperJS: c:\CasperJS (where c:\CasperJS\bin\casperjs.exe is present)
- PhantomJS:  c:\PhantomJS (where c:\PhantomJS\bin\phantomjs.exe is present)
- ImageMagick:  c:\ImageMagick  (where c:\ImageMagick\convert.exe is present)

IMPORTANT: BothCasperJS/PhantomJS have issues handlings paces in paths/filenames and so if you install any component to a path that contains a space, or have Splunk installed somewhere other than ‘Program Files’ that also contains a space, the app will fail to initialise.

IMPORTANT: This App captures PDF renders exactly as displayed in browser, and so these may contain sensitive data. Please be aware of this when exporting data.